<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1323,884,1270]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">HOST PLANTS. Filicopsida: uncertain (see below); highly polyphagous on Angiospermae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1323,884,1270]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
COMMENTS. The record of this species being associated with ferns is due to 
<bibRefCitation author="Schneider, J." firstAuthor="Schneider" journalOrPublisher="Phytoma" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="26 - 32" part="18" refId="ref7551" refString="Schneider, J. (1966) Ennemis des fougeres ornementales. Phytoma, 18, 26 - 32." title="Ennemis des fougeres ornementales" type="journal article" year="1966">
Schneider (
<number box="[273,335,1084,1110]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1966.0">1966</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, subsequently quoted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gerson, U." box="[640,813,1084,1110]" firstAuthor="Gerson" journalOrPublisher="Fern Gazette" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="29 - 45" part="12" refId="ref6804" refString="Gerson, U. (1979) The associations between Pteridophytes and Arthropods. Fern Gazette, 12, 29 - 45." title="The associations between Pteridophytes and Arthropods" type="journal article" year="1979">
Gerson (
<number box="[741,804,1084,1110]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, Schneider gave no specific fernfeeding records, but discussed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[628,822,1124,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Trialeurodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaporariorum">
<emphasis box="[628,822,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">T. vaporariorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a general pest of greenhouse plants: he did imply that ferns also suffered the attentions of this pest, through mentioning its polyphagy within an article on fern pests under glass. We are not aware of any authenticated record of the glasshouse whitefly colonising any pteridophyte.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
